<title>USA: California Amplifier co-founder resigns.</title>
<headline>California Amplifier co-founder resigns.</headline>
<dateline>CAMARILLO, Calif. 1996-08-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>California Amplifier Inc said on Tuesday that David Nichols, an executive vice-president who co-founded the company in 1981, resigned to pursue personal interests.</p>
<p>The company also said Allyn Hall has joined the firm as director of the company's broadband scrambling technology.</p>
<p>Shares of California Amplifier closed 1/8 lower at 7-7/8 on the Nasdaq.</p>
